The Fortran code must read each string as a token, not a line. Wait, in the first Java program, the code is:

for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
    String str = in.next();
    ... 
} So in.next() reads the next token, splitting on whitespace. So in Fortran, to read each string as a token, we can use list-directed input. So instead of reading with '(A)', which reads the entire line, perhaps we should read with read(*,*) str, but that may have issues with strings containing spaces.
